.TITLE
BODY
.HELP
			Function and Format
	
	Function:

	    BODY signals the start of executable commands
	    in a procedure.


	Format:

	    BODY
.PAGE
			Usage Notes


	o  BODY terminates the declaration section of the
	   procedure;  declarations (e.g. LOCAL or PARM) are
	   not permitted after BODY.

	o  BODY is permitted only in a procedure. It must be
	   present even if the procedure has no parameters.

.END
